{
  "texts": [
    "• Ensure that students, faculty, and staff will have secure, affordable access to generative AI.",
    "If access is already provided, evaluate the degree to which it has been leveraged and barriers to further adoption.",
    "• Prioritize developing more robust policies and nuanced vocabularies for generative AI use and disclosure in research and scholarly communication.",
    "Seek opportunities to build consensus with peer organizations and scholarly communities to promote baseline best practices and consistent terminology when possible.",
    "• Support long-term research in the scholarship of teaching and learning to provide the empirical evidence necessary to make datadriven decisions about AI and pedagogy."
  ]
}